President Biden has nominated Ajay Banga, a business leader with experience in developing countries and addressing financial inclusion and climate change, to be President of the World Bank. Ajay Banga is known for his successful management of global companies and his ability to forge public-private partnerships. He has a track record of mobilizing resources to tackle urgent challenges such as climate change. Banga's background in India gives him a unique perspective on the opportunities and challenges facing developing countries. He currently serves as Vice Chairman at General Atlantic and was previously President and CEO of Mastercard. Banga has also held leadership positions in various organizations and has received several awards for his contributions.